<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><recipe><recipe-name>White Chicken Chile</recipe-name><description>A brothy chicken chilly with corn and beans.</description><ingredients><Ingredient><ingredient-name>Chicken Breasts</ingredient-name><amount>1</amount><measurement>lb</measurement></Ingredient><Ingredient><ingredient-name>Chicken broth</ingredient-name><amount>2</amount><measurement>cans</measurement></Ingredient><Ingredient><ingredient-name>Rotel tomatoes</ingredient-name><amount>1</amount><measurement>can</measurement></Ingredient><Ingredient><ingredient-name>Chile powder</ingredient-name><amount>2</amount><measurement>tsp</measurement></Ingredient><Ingredient><ingredient-name>Shoepeg Corn</ingredient-name><amount>1</amount><measurement>cna</measurement></Ingredient><Ingredient><ingredient-name>White northern beans</ingredient-name><amount>1</amount><measurement>can</measurement></Ingredient><instructions>Add chicken, broth, rotel, and chile powder to crockpot. Cook on low for 4-5 hours. Use forks to shred the chicken, and the can of corn (drained) and the can of beans (undrained). Stir well, and cook for an additional 45 minutes.</instructions></ingredients></recipe>